verbose_text: Results showed that CIRP protein was expressed in all 3 types of pituitary adenoma tissues, but with different levels : non invasive adenoma had the lowest CIRP proteins; invasive pituitary adenoma had significantly higher CIRP protein levels compared to non invasive tumors with statistical significance (p < 0.05); and CIRP protein expression was further elevated for recurrent pituitary adenoma with statistically significant difference compared to non recurrent tumors (p < 0.05) as shown in XREF_FIG and XREF_FIG.
